de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.particity.service.persistence

Class AHCategoriesUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.particity.service.persistence.AHCategoriesUtil

  • public class AHCategoriesUtil
extends Object
    The persistence utility for the a h categories service. This utility wraps AHCategoriesPersistenceImpl and provides direct access to the database for CRUD operations. This utility should only be used by the service layer, as it must operate within a transaction. Never access this utility in a JSP, controller, model, or other front-end class.

    Caching information and settings can be found in portal.properties

    Author:
    Brian Wing Shun Chan
    See Also:
    AHCategoriesPersistence, AHCategoriesPersistenceImpl

      • findBynameAndType

        public static List<AHCategories> findBynameAndType(String name,
                                                   int type,
                                                   int start,
                                                   int end)
                                            throws com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException
        Returns a range of all the a h categorieses where name = ? and type = ?.

        Useful when paginating results. Returns a maximum of end - start instances. start and end are not primary keys, they are indexes in the result set. Thus, 0 refers to the first result in the set. Setting both start and end to QueryUtil.ALL_POS will return the full result set. If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil.ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.particity.model.impl.AHCategoriesModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.

        Parameters:
        name - the name
        type - the type
        start - the lower bound of the range of a h categorieses
        end - the upper bound of the range of a h categorieses (not inclusive)
        Returns:
        the range of matching a h categorieses
        Throws:
        com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException - if a system exception occurred

      • findBytype

        public static List<AHCategories> findBytype(int type,
                                            int start,
                                            int end)
                                     throws com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException
        Returns a range of all the a h categorieses where type = ?.

        Useful when paginating results. Returns a maximum of end - start instances. start and end are not primary keys, they are indexes in the result set. Thus, 0 refers to the first result in the set. Setting both start and end to QueryUtil.ALL_POS will return the full result set. If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil.ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.particity.model.impl.AHCategoriesModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.

        Parameters:
        type - the type
        start - the lower bound of the range of a h categorieses
        end - the upper bound of the range of a h categorieses (not inclusive)
        Returns:
        the range of matching a h categorieses
        Throws:
        com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException - if a system exception occurred

      • findAll

        public static List<AHCategories> findAll(int start,
                                         int end)
                                  throws com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException
        Returns a range of all the a h categorieses.

        Useful when paginating results. Returns a maximum of end - start instances. start and end are not primary keys, they are indexes in the result set. Thus, 0 refers to the first result in the set. Setting both start and end to QueryUtil.ALL_POS will return the full result set. If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil.ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.particity.model.impl.AHCategoriesModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.

        Parameters:
        start - the lower bound of the range of a h categorieses
        end - the upper bound of the range of a h categorieses (not inclusive)
        Returns:
        the range of a h categorieses
        Throws:
        com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException - if a system exception occurred

If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.
